delete sequences with imported waits and
controller-local policy.
service: marketplace
slug: acceptedagreement
kind: AcceptedAgreement
archetype: generated-service-manager
status/finalizer: required /
retain-until-confirmed-delete
requeue: terminating
provider states: create none; update none;
delete none
supported drift: defined_tags, display_name,
freeform_tags
reject before mutate: force-new fields
agreement_id, compartment_id, listing_id,
package_version (+1 more)
create-only fields: none
list lookup: oci_marketplace_accepted_agreements
filters agreement_id, compartment_id,
display_name, listing_id (+1 more)
conflicts: none
open gaps: none
AcceptedAgreement reuses an existing OCI
agreement before create by exact compartmentId,
listingId, packageVersion, and agreementId
match, with displayName narrowing when set.
OCI accepted agreement responses do not expose
lifecycle state, so successful create and update
normalize directly to Active from the immediate
response body.
In-place updates are limited to displayName,
definedTags, and freeformTags; agreementId,
compartmentId, listingId, packageVersion, and
signature are replacement-only.
The controller mirrors the last applied
signature at status.appliedSignature because OCI
read models never return the signature needed
for explicit drift checks.
Delete retains the finalizer until
DeleteAcceptedAgreement is followed by
GetAcceptedAgreement returning not found.
end note
